foliation.p: Foliated in the bottom margins. Traces of a pagination on top outer corners.

layout.p: Written in one column with 26 to 31 lines per page. Running titles on fols 2r-46r.

handNote.p: Written by Sigurður Jónsson of Knörr.

accMat.p: On fol. 59 in AM 597 b 4to there is a table of contents regarding the excerpts and extracts of Hauksbók in AM 281 4to.

origin.p: Written in Iceland at the end of the seventeenth century. It is possible that the manuscript was written for Sigurður Björnsson at Saurbær (Kjalarnes).

acquisition.p: According to a letter to Jón Halldórsson in 1729 (Jón Margeirsson, Bréf Árna Magnússonar til Íslands 1729 og fleiri skjöl hans í Ríkisskjalasafni Dana 147 ), Árni Magnússon got the manuscript from Sigurður Björnsson at Saurbær (Kjalarnes), brother-in-law of the manuscript's scribe.
